commitResults.messageBody:
Implements task filters and the relevant GUI.

TaskFilters class contains TaskFilters which each represent a filter.
Selected filters are shown as "chips" in the GUI, which can be removed
by clicking the "x" button.

Model and Logic classes have additional setters and getters for the
list of available and selected task filters.

commitResults.messageBody:
Introduce bug fixes for:
- Editing a task not updating available filters
- Allowing for current filter to remain even after purge (to remain
consistent with behaviour from Done/Undone filters). The filter is
stil removed from the list of available filters

Removed the functionality of Done/Undone not being in the filter list
if there are no done/undone tasks respectively.

Existing bugs yet to be fixed:
- Suppose tag A is a subset of tag B, purging all when filtering by
tag A causes the dropdown filter list to display an extra empty box.

commitResults.messageBody:
Current implementation during editing of AB3 Persons is that
all with the previous name will be marked as not in AB3, while tasks
with the new edited name will be marked as in AB3. The names in Contact
will NOT be updated to the edited name as of this commit.
